  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6831 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6820 (-20.3B) and max positive gamma at 6840 (+25.5B), dealers are likely covering short delta positions as spot approaches the positive gamma wall, creating buying pressure that should cap upside momentum near 6840. The PIN regime with 34.6B total GEX suggests dealers will aggressively sell any push above 6840 and buy any dip toward 6820, creating a tight trading range with mean reversion characteristics. The massive GEX surge event combined with the 6863 flip strike just above current levels means any breakout above 6850 (+25.0B wall) faces significant dealer selling pressure.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect prices to chop between 6820-6840 with dealers capping both sides.",
